<subSubSection pageId="29" pageNumber="30" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1264,1458]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[208,336,1306,1332]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Body vermiform; scapular tubercles and setae on rear shield margin, scapular setae (
<emphasis box="[1402,1426,1307,1332]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">sc</emphasis>
) directed posteriorly; femur I seta absent, tibial seta absent, empodium entire.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="29.[151,1436,1264,1458]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">
This genus consists of 87 species (
<bibRefCitation author="Amrine, J. W. Jr. &amp; Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W." box="[610,837,1390,1416]" pageId="29" pageNumber="30" refId="ref44790" refString="Amrine, J. W. Jr., Stasny, T. A. &amp; Flechtmann, C. H. W. (2003) Revised keys to world genera of Eriophyoidea (Acari: Prostigmata). Indira Publishing House, Michigan, U. S. A., 244 pp." type="book" year="2003">
Amrine 
<emphasis box="[708,760,1390,1415]" italics="true" pageId="29" pageNumber="30">et al</emphasis>
. 2003
</bibRefCitation>
). Three species have been recorded from Southeast Asia.
</paragraph>
